Swiss Financial Crises Committee Meets, NZZ am Sonntag Says

-- B y   E l e n a   L o g u t e n k o v a
-- 
2011-10-09T09:44:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/swiss-financial-crises-committee-meets-nzz-am-sonntag-says.html
The Swiss financial crises committee
will start meetings to discuss the possible effects of
bankruptcy of a European country on  UBS AG (UBSN) ,  Credit Suisse Group
AG (CSGN)  and risks for  Switzerland ,  NZZ am Sonntag  reported, citing
two unidentified people.  All major world banks would be affected by Greek bankruptcy
through second and third-round effects, Patrick Raaflaub, head
of the Swiss Financial Market Supervisory Authority, told the
newspaper. Raaflaub, who heads the financial crises committee,
declined to comment about the committeeâ€™s activities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
